00:20:50,247 --> 00:20:51,708
Yeah, no, I think it's a great point.

316
00:20:52,708 --> 00:20:59,671
And we of course see this happen all the time when developers roll out patches that the

317
00:20:59,732 --> 00:21:01,072
community isn't prepared for.

318
00:21:01,492 --> 00:21:03,033
Sometimes right before a tournament.

319
00:21:03,073 --> 00:21:04,154
So you're right.

320
00:21:04,174 --> 00:21:06,876
I mean in some ways it's a very precarious playing field.

321
00:21:07,336 --> 00:21:10,298
Of course it's worth keeping in mind that in traditional sports,

322
00:21:11,018 --> 00:21:14,060
equipment also changes and can change the shape of play.

323
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:17,222
But I think one of the key things there is that

324
00:21:17,322 --> 00:21:22,185
especially as developers decide that they want to be more involved in eSports,

325
00:21:22,465 --> 00:21:27,288
that they have to be sensitive for the ways those ripple effects kind of work through the community.

