00:22:10,847 --> 00:22:15,848
So, my feeling right now when it comes to the IP stuff in games is that

336
00:22:17,089 --> 00:22:20,890
developers are generally happy if people tinker,

337
00:22:21,730 --> 00:22:24,811
as long as it's non-commercial and or doesn't affect the brand.

338
00:22:26,231 --> 00:22:30,653
And I think both of those are insufficient models for cultural production.

339
00:22:31,313 --> 00:22:35,734
So I both think people have a right to make money off of remix-reuse,

340
00:22:36,855 --> 00:22:38,215
that that is the work of culture.

341
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:40,901
We are always working over artifacts.

342
00:22:42,963 --> 00:22:48,207
And that if you really want to take games seriously as a cultural product or a sports product,

343
00:22:48,867 --> 00:22:52,790
that you can't always control the brand.

344
00:22:53,171 --> 00:23:00,416
So, I think the battles around this are, we're probably much more likely to see them through the live streaming stuff that's happening.

345
00:23:01,938 --> 00:23:08,663
But yeah, I'd like to see, I would like to see co-creative models really flourish a lot more than they do right now.

