00:23:46,942 --> 00:23:48,103
Is this for the bromance?

359
00:23:48,743 --> 00:23:50,565
So what do you think eSport is?

360
00:23:51,561 --> 00:23:53,663
All of the above and in different iterations.

361
00:23:54,283 --> 00:23:57,407
So I think it can vary over the life of a player.

362
00:23:58,207 --> 00:24:01,050
I think it can vary over the context of a scene.

363
00:24:01,150 --> 00:24:05,195
So in my experience interviewing pro players over the years,

364
00:24:06,156 --> 00:24:11,301
at the root of it is a fundamental passion for...

365
00:24:12,155 --> 00:24:15,616
not just competition, but getting and being better.

366
00:24:16,456 --> 00:24:21,178
And it is the thing, it's the thing that when I did MMO work, I sort of distinguished

367
00:24:21,659 --> 00:24:26,540
power gamers, like the folks who are willing to fail and go over and over and over again,

368
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:30,602
that fundamentally it's that. It's a thing I don't have. It's why I would give up after

369
00:24:30,642 --> 00:24:36,664
a handful of tries. But I think as people inhabit eSports spaces, of course you know,

370
00:24:37,410 --> 00:24:41,154
The fame, the glory, the satisfaction, that can all play a role.

371
00:24:41,214 --> 00:24:45,818
But fundamentally, at the root, I think it is something about this,

372
00:24:46,378 --> 00:24:50,923
usually a deep passion for the game and a deep passion to keep getting better.

